Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with language modeling and Part-of-Speech tagging, which are both sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP) that fall under the cs.CL category. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses multi-task learning, which is a machine learning technique, to improve language modeling. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - NLP and machine learning are both sub-fields of AI, and this paper uses techniques from both to improve code-switching language modeling. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses LSTM-based language models, which are a type of neural network, to model code-switching. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) - This category is less likely, but code-switching can also occur in spoken language, and the paper may have used audio data in addition to text data.
